<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 05 at 2:10PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
northern Smyth, Tazewell and southwestern Bland Counties through 245
PM EDT...
At 209 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Jewell Ridge, or near Richlands, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Richlands...
Tazewell...
Cedar Bluff...
Ceres...
Burkes Garden...
Nebo...
and Raven.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
